---
import Join from "../components/join.astro";
import Layout from "../components/layout.astro";
import PageHero from "../components/page-hero.astro";
import Section from "../components/ui/section.astro";
---

<Layout
  title="About · Epistola"
  description="Mission-driven organization: we build the best possible document software for public institutions at reasonable prices."
>
  <PageHero
    monoTitle="/ About"
    title="Built to serve, not to maximize"
    description="We're a small team that believes good software for municipalities shouldn't be held hostage by profit incentives."
  />

  <Section monoTitle="Who we are" title="A small team of founders running the company together">
    <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto flex flex-col gap-5 text-lg leading-relaxed text-[var(--color-peach-paper-copy)]">
      <p>
        Epistola is owned and operated by about five people who co-founded the organization. We're not a venture-backed
        startup chasing growth at all costs—we're a group of founders building software we believe in, together.
      </p>
      <p>
        We started Epistola because we saw municipalities struggling with document generation tools that were either
        expensive, inflexible, or locked them into vendor relationships. We wanted to create something better: reliable,
        open-source software that serves the public good.
      </p>
      <p>
        Everyone here is a founder in spirit. We make decisions together, we're accountable to each other, and we move
        forward as a unified team.
      </p>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section monoTitle="How we price" title="Budget-driven pricing, not profit maximization">
    <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto flex flex-col gap-5 text-lg leading-relaxed text-[var(--color-peach-paper-copy)]">
      <p>
        We set clear goals each year: what features we want to build, what infrastructure we need, what SLAs we
        commit to, and what team we can afford. We budget for those goals. Then we price the software to cover that
        budget—nothing more, nothing less.
      </p>
      <p>
        Our revenue comes from three streams: feature development, SLA contracts, and donations. Not every organization
        needs or wants an SLA, but we still maintain the software, ship security patches, and keep things running.
        These donations—we call them <em>levensvatbaarheidsbijdragen</em> (viability contributions)—help keep the
        project sustainable for everyone.
      </p>
      <p>
        If revenue grows beyond our budget, we have two choices: reinvest the surplus into the product and team, or
        reduce prices. Returns on investment are capped—we don't accumulate profit to maximize shareholder returns.
      </p>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Section
    monoTitle="The future"
    title="Formalizing our mission with a foundation"
  >
    <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto flex flex-col gap-5 text-lg leading-relaxed text-[var(--color-peach-paper-copy)]">
      <p>
        Today, our commitment to this mission rests on the values and promises of our founders. But we want to make it
        permanent. We're working toward creating a foundation (stichting) that will legally guard this mission for the
        long term.
      </p>
      <p>
        The foundation will ensure that no future change of ownership or direction can override our core principles: fair
        pricing, open development, and service to the public good. Until then, we operate by the same principles and
        personally vouch for them.
      </p>
    </div>
  </Section>

  <Join />
</Layout>
